# Policy Structure:
The policy is a **linear priority dispatch rule**: **Score = W · features(order)**

- **params** is a {{ rank }}-dimensional weight vector
- **W**: {{ rank }} weights — one per dispatch feature
- All candidate orders are scored with the weight vector and ranked uniformly
- **params** values are constrained to [-5.0, 5.0] with 4 decimal places
- At each step, the candidate order with the **highest priority score** is dispatched

**Feature-Weight Mapping (params[0]~params[9] correspond to these features):**
| Index | Feature | Meaning | Typical Good Sign |
|-------|---------|---------|-------------------|
| 0 | dest_supply_shortage | Destination driver shortage | Positive (go to scarce areas) |
| 1 | order_price | Order fare | Positive (prefer high-value) |
| 2 | duration_cost | Trip duration | Negative (penalize long trips) |
| 3 | price_efficiency | Fare per minute | Positive (prefer efficient trips) |
| 4 | real_order_bias | Real vs virtual order | Positive (prefer real orders) |
| 5 | current_grid_push | Local grid congestion | Positive (leave congested areas) |
| 6 | dest_order_pull | Destination order density | Positive (go to order hotspots) |
| 7 | cross_grid_penalty | Cross-grid movement | Negative (avoid cross-grid) |
| 8 | global_imbalance | Supply-demand imbalance | Positive (correct imbalance) |
| 9 | mdp_advantage | Long-term RL value | Positive (consider future) |

